sql:
SELECT users.user_id, users.username, users.full_name, analytics.engagement_rate
FROM users
INNER JOIN analytics ON users.user_id = analytics.user_id;

external_knowledge:
- "Shine the brightest" in the context of social media refers to posts with the highest engagement; 
- "Social media garden" is a metaphor for the space where user-generated content is shared and interacted with; 
- "Seeds of content" symbolize the initial posts made by users; 
- "Draw the largest crowd" is a metaphor for gaining the most engagement, such as likes, comments, and shares.

sql:
SELECT AVG(total_engagement_count) AS average_ocean_depth
FROM (
    SELECT SUM(engagement_count) AS total_engagement_count
    FROM engagement
    GROUP BY user_id
) AS user_engagement_totals;

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM followers 
INNER JOIN users ON followers.user_id = users.user_id;

SELECT user_id, COUNT(*) AS num_followers
FROM followers
GROUP BY user_id;
